		<body>
		<pb n="1"/>
		
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>St. Thomas</placeName> <date>7<hi rend="sup">th</hi> March 1848</date>.</p>
			<p><addressee>Revd Mr Leeser</addressee></p>
		  <p rend="indent(1)">My Dr Sir</p>
		  <p rend="indent(2)">I thank you exceedingly for all<lb/> your letters &amp; having no important subject to write<lb/> upon have deferred until this moment</p>
		  <p rend="indent(1)">I have retained the Priasah[&#63;] Books sent by you<lb/> for <persName>Carvalhos</persName> friend at <placeName>Grenada</placeName>.  I do not know him &amp;<lb/> the changes in the <placeName>English Islands</placeName> are so great that<lb/> I doubt if the amount would be forthcoming besides the<lb/> route of the Steamer has been changed.  I hold them to<lb/> your order in the mean time will endeavor to dispose of<lb/> them.</p>
		  <p rend="indent(1)">My family regret the demise of <persName>Mrs Phillips</persName> enclosed<lb/> a letter for <persName>Madelaine</persName> which please deliver</p>
		  <p rend="indent(1)">You will have read of the death of the late<lb/> <persName>King of <placeName>Denmark</placeName> Christian the 8&#39;</persName>. &amp; the succession of his<lb/> Son <persName>Frederic the 7th</persName> we had a particular service on<lb/> <date>Sunday</date> Evening last for the [&#63;] of his soul the<lb/> Synagogue was filled by all classes &amp; coulours&#44; <persName>Mr Nathan</persName><lb/> was happy enough to compose a Sermon or Discourse<lb/> that was highly satisfactory to all present&#95;&#95;it has done<lb/> done us good service.  We are at present quiet&#44; the<lb/> Laws not yet returned from <placeName>Copenhagen</placeName>.  I suppose that<lb/> the Kings death will be a cause of detention to them</p>
		  <p rend="indent(1)">Have you seen <persName>Mr Carillons</persName> refutation to <persName>Mr<lb/> Pennocks</persName> affectionate address to the Jews of <placeName>Jamaica&#63;</placeName><lb/>  it is a master piece.  the Books are bought up as fast<lb/> as they can be printed&#44; they have been sent to <placeName>Europe</placeName><lb/> &amp; thro the <placeName>West Indies</placeName>.  his bitterest enemies&#44; award him</p>

		<pb n="2"/>
		
			<p>applause &amp; merit</p>
			<p>My Son <persName>Danie</persName> &amp; his Wife gone to the <placeName>US</placeName><lb/> to reside he will determine <del>while</del> after his arrival which<lb/> city he will select for his abode &#44; he is a religious &amp; worthy<lb/> young man &amp; I recommend him highly to you&#44; he is my<lb/> son &amp; will not [&#63;] all I feel he deserves&#59;&#8211;it will<lb/> cost me great pain to put with him my consolation is<lb/> that he will succeed in <placeName>America</placeName>&#44; his mind being firmly<lb/> bent upon living in that happy country</p>
		  <p rend="indent(4)">I am with regards from my family</p>
		  <p rend="indent(5)">Yours Sincerely</p>
		  <p rend="indent(6)"><persName role="author">A. Wolff</persName></p>

			<p><persName>Mr Isaacs</persName> writes me from <placeName>New York</placeName> that one of <persName>Dr.<lb/> Lininthal&#39;s</persName> congregation has put him in &#34;Hesem&#34; is<lb/> this permitted in <placeName>America</placeName>&#63;  to put any one in Hesem&#63;<lb/>  &amp; above all&#44; is it permitted that a lay body should<lb/> <hi rend="underline">dare</hi> to excommunicate its Spiritual head&#63;  I suppose<lb/> like all our benighted Rulers &amp; Wardens or Trustees as you<lb/> may call them&#44; they have constituted themselves.  Accuses<lb/> [&#63;] &amp; Judges&#59; &amp; I suppose if this great Body be<lb/> <sic>annalized</sic> it would be found to be composed of Old Clothes<lb/> men&#44; Ignorant &amp; <sic>arogant</sic>&#95;shame upon us&#95;I trust that<lb/> the Dr. will treat them with the contempt they deserve by<lb/> depriving them of his [&#63;] &amp; abilities the cause <persName>M Isaac</persName><lb/> writes is for transferring some of their by laws&#59; it can be<lb/> nothing that Crime is attached to&#44; or it would have<lb/> been blazoned about&#44; do write the particulars.</p>

		<pb n="3"/>
		
			<p><addressee>Revd Mr Leeser</addressee></p>
		  <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
